Dialogs.Dialog: Take it to the staff room. Within a week.
Well, that's okay. It's just a side trip.
I leave it to you. I don't want to go near the staff room.
Do it yourself. You're here on business, aren't you, ▲小早川＊▲？
(I have to deliver the note, where did you say the teacher was, ▲小早川＊▲？)
The one you took with you.
Ah, the one you asked me about before. I gave it to the Sensei.
Why didn't you take it with you？
Oh... somehow, I couldn't get the timing right...
Hey, do the book club member's job for me.
I don't want to do that.
(Oh, by the way, you asked me to take over your job, ▲小早川＊▲...)
(I'm working on your behalf today, again, ▲小早川＊▲...)
Just take it easy and go
You really took over my job.
I made a promise, in case you're wondering.
You skipped work. I told you to take over.
I just had a teacher get mad at me.
(Well, I guess it's bad enough that I broke my promise...)
Make a list of unreturned items by the end of the next three days.
Well, just think of it as another learning experience for the committee members.
I can't do it, even if you tell me suddenly.
(By the way, you asked me to make an unreturned list, ▲小早川＊▲.)
(I need to make the list you asked me to make, ▲小早川＊▲...)
Just take it easy and go
You got it right, the unreturned list.
Well, yeah, I was pretty desperate.
You didn't finish the unreturned list.
Oh... I was a little short on time...
Hey. What kind of music do you listen to ▲小早川＊▲？
...even if I tell you, you won't get it.
Maybe I'll understand when I hear it, you know？
...Hah, if you feel up to it. Why don't you call on me again？
All right, let me hear it again sometime. Promise.
Not making any promises, but... do what you want.
Well, if you don't feel like it now, then fine.
(By the way, I should ask you about the music you enjoy listening to, ▲小早川＊▲...)
(I wonder if you'd let me listen to your music today, ▲小早川＊▲...)
Go to the library right away
Take my time and look for her
Hah, you want to hear it that bad？
(I think she looks a little happy... maybe I'm just imagining it.)
And you never showed up after all.
I don't mind. I don't want to force you to listen to it either.
Is the Library Enhancement Week about to begin？
Yes. So don't skip out on your committee work.
I don't think I was on duty...
I know that without being told.
I don't think I was on duty during that period...
...so you're the only one slacking off while I'm busy.
(I have to make it to the Library Enhancement Week...)
(Still Library Enhancement Week... I should get to work.)
Go to the library right now
I'll be fine if I take it easy
Finally, the end of the reinforcement week. Good work this week, ▲小早川＊▲.
We don't work so much that it's exhausting, though, at least not for me.
Really？ Yes, it went more smoothly than I had imagined.
...just because someone I thought was out of the line of fire was surprisingly helpful.
Newcomers who don't do their job, are the worst.
Ah, sorry... the Library Enhancement Week...
Sleepy... just send me a text every morning to wake me up, even if it's just for a week.
Okay, that sounds fun. But does it take more than a text to wake you up？
Why me... Wouldn't it be faster to have a family member wake you up？
(Huh？ Are you in a bad mood？)
(By the way, you asked me to wake you up via email, ▲小早川＊▲.)
Thanks to your meddling, I might not have overslept.
For now, I'll just say thanks.
You are... so useless for meddling. You never send me emails after all.
No, I didn't count on it from the beginning.
That's right. They are going to have a meeting to improve the work of the Library Committee for a while.
I agree, but I heard attendance is a must.
I see. Well, it can't be helped.
This also means it's the duty of the committee members. Don't slack off.
I'm a little busy... so I can't.
So that's how you pretend to be busy. That's unfair.
(Oh, there was a business improvement meeting for the Library Committee members...)
(There was a business improvement meeting for the Library Committee...)
Go to the library right away
It'll be fine if I take it easy
Well, yeah. What was this all about, anyway？
Who knows. Isn't that a teacher's whim？ Good grief.
You didn't come to the Library Committee meetings.
The sensei's mood is bad because of your absence, and I'm not happy about it.
Do you go straight home when you leave school, ▲小早川＊▲？
That's not what I meant, but I can't help but wonder.
Hmm. If you don't trust me, will you follow me？
I'm not busy. Maybe I will
It's not that big of a deal
Maybe I will, I'm not busy.
What. If it's no good, don't say it from the beginning.
I didn't say no... I don't mind.
Well, I guess I'll do it for a while.
Yes, yes, have it your way.
(It doesn't sound like you really don't want to...)
Better not. It doesn't bother me that much.
(Oh, I mentioned I would go home with you this week... where are you, ▲小早川＊▲.)
(I'll go home with you again... where are you, ▲小早川＊▲.)
Of course not. Well, that's a relief.
Don't worry about it. That's enough, later.
I thought you were going to follow me home.
Well... well, there were a lot of inconveniences.
(Maybe I should have done as I said.)
There are a lot of books that haven't been returned.
...I guess I should go around and collect.
You don't have to go that far
It's going to be quite a challenge to round them all.
Maybe we need to break it up into several days.
You don't have to go that far...
(By the way, I'm supposed to collect unreturned books... where are you ▲小早川＊▲？)
(I'll be collecting unreturned books today too... where are you, ▲小早川＊▲？)
Go to the library right now
She could be in the classroom
Have we gone all the way around？
We may have recovered more than we thought.
A lot of people brought it with them but couldn't be bothered to return them.
What you borrow, you have to return. That's common sense. Well, anyway, good job.
You were going to let me collect it all by myself, weren't you？
So you're all talk and no sense of responsibility？
Have you been going to the arcade lately？ You're going to worry me if you stay up late playing.
Shut up... life guidance is overdue.
If you're worried, you can come and keep an eye on me.
Okay, you said it. I'm really going to be there.
Then, I'll show up. I won't get in the way.
No way. I'm not going to do that. That really sounds like a life guidance teacher, doesn't it？
(I wonder if you're going to the arcade today... I'll go check on you, ▲小早川＊▲.)
(I wonder if you're in the arcade today... I should see how you're doing, ▲小早川＊▲.)
You come here often. That's enough.
Yeah. It doesn't seem that dangerous.
You worry too much. You are too meddlesome.
Don't say that. Just be careful.
In the end, you didn't show up at the arcade.
Then that's fine, it'd be annoying to have you there.
Hey, I'm a member of the Library Committee, but I'm basically free. Why don't we have a competition to see who can read more books while doing more work？
This is no time to play
A match. All right, I won't lose！
Hehe, you think you can beat Rinko that easily？
Saying that... this is no time to play around, right？
Yes, yes, you're a serious guy.
(By the way, we have a competition to see how many books we can read... what shall I read, ▲小早川＊▲？)
(We are competing to see how many books we can read... what shall I read, ▲小早川＊▲？)
...you read that much, you're good at it.
I guess... not as much as you ▲小早川＊▲.
That, you see, is the difference between professionals and amateurs.
I mean you did well for an amateur. Well, it was a good way to pass the time.
That's not good at all. It's less than a tenth of Rinko's.
(I guess that's what I get for skipping work...)
I found kittens behind the school building, three of them. I didn't see any parent cats... do they live there？
Eh？ Well, Rinko will look for a foster family, so until then, let's both take care of them together.
Yes, let's do it. I can't leave them alone.
Done！ I'll pick you up every morning starting tomorrow, bring milk and feed.
Okay, I've got it. What would you like as feed？
You have a can of mackerel.
I'm kidding. Well, then, that's that.
Hmm～... I think I'd get emotional if I did that...
(By the way, we're supposed to take care of the cats, ▲小早川＊▲...)
(Today, we will take care of the cats too, ▲小早川＊▲...)
I found a foster home for the kittens.
We had a hard time with this.
Good work. But, aren't you feeling lonely, ▲小早川＊▲？
Well... a bit. But the kitty's happiness is the best.
The kitten behind the school building are gone...
(I guess I should have looked at them properly...)
When asked about the contents of a book in the library, it's difficult to give a quick explanation, isn't it？
Then, do you want to put an "explanation card" in the books that are often asked about？
Do your best, huh... you're gonna help me, aren't you？
Because you're the one who suggested it.
All right. Then let's do it together！
That's a pain in the ass...
Then why don't you do something about it yourself？
(I'm sorry you went through the trouble...)
(By the way, we're supposed to make explanation cards for books, ▲小早川＊▲...)
(We have to make another explanation card today...)
Go to the library right now
The explanation card is done. It's pretty good.
You're one of the hard workers, aren't you？ Hehe.
This would make it more convenient for borrowers.
I wonder why we didn't have it before. Past Library Committee members have been so unkind.
Did you intend from the beginning to make the explanation card and force Rinko to do it？
Well, then, you should have helped me.
You know, there are often advertising pop-ups in bookstores.
Yeah, some of them are pretty elaborate.
I wonder if something like that could be done by the Library Committee.
Could be interesting, we should try to make one.
Then it's settled. I won't allow any compromises, so be prepared.
Hmm, I feel like that's a bit much.
(By the way, you said we should make a pop-up ad for the Library, ▲小早川＊▲...)
(Okay, we'll make another book pop-up today...)
Go to the library right now
Good job. You made it look good.
Good job to you, too. I'm pretty sure this will please everyone, ▲小早川＊▲.
It's as good as any store out there.
I might have a good sense, haha.
Hah？ What are you talking about.
(I guess I got too carried away... I'm I did this, though.)
It's kind of half-baked and uncool...
That's because you cut corners, hah...
How's it going with your family these days？
Anyway, are you free for a while？ I'd like you to keep me company for the night...
Dad says he can come home early at night for a while from now on. That's unusual.
Then you should have a family gathering...
That's true. I think they need to spend some time together.
I don't know about my little brother, but if Rinko were there, he would be concerned.
That's what I mean. Well, if I can kill time in a park or something, I'm fine.
You think I'm always free, don't you？ That's not necessarily true, ▲小早川＊▲.
Oh, I see... then I won't ask, so that's fine.
(By the way, you asked me to go out with you tonight, ▲小早川＊▲...)
Thanks for hanging out with me.
Thanks to that, those two are looking good.
But... do you understand Rinko's concern？
I'm sure you're aware of that, probably.
You didn't come and... ended up killing time by yourself.
Ah... I did a bad thing, sorry.
It's really bad. If you can't make a promise, don't make it in the first place.
(I think I'll call her a little different. Last name, first name, san or chan...)
(I was turned down, but I'm not sure if this is the best way to call you.)
(...you ignored me？ I guess I shouldn't have called you that.)
Are you sure？ Then let's go.
(Looks like the way I call you now is fine.)
Since we're here, let's go together.
(Looks like the way I called you it's fine.)
Since we're here, why don't we go together？
Why don't you just follow me... on your own？
(Looks like the way I called you it's fine.)
Are you alone？ Come with me if you want.
(Looks like the way I called you it's fine.)
(▲高嶺＊＊▲... I'll try to talk with her.)
That really surprised me... it was only you, ▲小早川＊▲.
I had some business with ▲高嶺＊＊▲
I was looking for you ▲小早川＊▲
(▲姉ヶ崎＊▲... I'll try talking to her.)
Sorry, I had to run an errand for someone I know...
Sorry, I was just about to talk about something with ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Hmm... so Rinko is in the way. Okay, then...
Sorry, I was just about to talk about something with ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲.
Yeah. I was looking for you ▲小早川＊▲...
Yeah, that's the book. It's refreshing.
Oh, I see, good for you... I'll be going now.
(You seem to be in a bad mood...)
What do you want？ I'm in a hurry.
Oh, I see... Well, I'll see you later.
It was a surprise, but I was in a hurry... Well, I'll be on my way.
(Oh, I'll try to talk to ▲高嶺＊＊▲.)
Eh！？ Ah, it's just you, ▲小早川＊▲.
What's with that reaction, your excitement is going down.
I'm here to see you ▲小早川＊▲
(Oh, I'll try to talk to ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲.)
I was just now trying to talk to someone I know.
Oh, I see... sorry to interrupt. Bye.
Hey, I need to go talk with ▲高嶺＊＊▲...
You don't need Rinko, do you？ Sorry to interrupt. See you later.
Hey, I need to go talk with ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲...
Ah, just in time. I wanted to ask you something, ▲小早川＊▲.
...really？ Well, I'm just willing to listen to you.
I see... you're so reliable ▲小早川＊▲.
Don't ask a younger girl to help you. I'm going.
Maybe this isn't the time to talk to Rinko, you know？
I don't have time for this either.
(Ah, you're here... I'll try to talk to you ▲高嶺＊＊▲.)
I'm here to see you ▲小早川＊▲
(Ah, you're here... I'll try to talk to you ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲.)
You don't need me, do you？ I have business with someone I know.
Nothing you say... I'm going now because I need to see someone.
Nothing you say... that's right. I had something to do with you ▲小早川＊▲.
Oh, so that was it. I'm glad I asked you, ▲小早川＊▲.
(Um, I was going to talk to ▲高嶺＊＊▲...)
(Um, I was going to talk to ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲...)
What？ Time is running out because you're lingering.
(What was that？ I guess you're gone too, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.)
(What was that？ I guess you're gone too, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲.)
Ah, you surprised me... so you were here too, ▲小早川＊▲.
I've been here for a while now...
I'm here to see you ▲小早川＊▲
I didn't notice... what's up？ I was looking for someone I know.
Yes, yes, I'm sorry to bother you. Bye.
What can I do for you？ I need to talk to someone I know...
...I don't have any use for you. Idiot.
I see... I'll be going. Sorry.
Just in time, I had some business with you, ▲小早川＊▲.
Ok, so that's how it is. That makes sense.
If you're convinced, I'll go now.
Oh, thank you！ See you soon.
(I guess it's no longer worth looking for her...)
Not that I was waiting for you... I'm going to go now. Bye.
Sorry, I didn't realize. Okay, I'll hurry up.
You don't have to worry about that... I'll be going.
Are you okay？ I think you got hurt...
I didn't... I was just surprised.
Are you sure？ Don't hold back, okay？
Sorry！ Well, I'm in a hurry, so I'll go.
Well... don't worry. I'm in a hurry.
...I'm fine. See you... I'm in a hurry.
(...why did you call me out then？)
Look, I have to go now.
I'm in a hurry. I'm going.
I was kind of in a daze...
Hey, I'm not always in a daze.
Oh... I was in a daze. What was it？
Geez... it's enough. Rinko has to go...
Oh, I see. See you later.
Hmm... you really are a free spirit, huh. See you.
Not that there's anything special going on.
I have an errand to run. See you later.
...Oh, my bad. I guess I stalled you somehow.
...Oh, sorry. I guess I got in your way.
That's okay, not that I'm busy.
What's the matter？ You wanted to see me？
What's the matter？ Were you waiting for me？
Should I have been doing something？
Well, I've got to go somewhere.
...Oh, I was kind of spaced out. Did you have something to do？
Nothing comes to mind. See you.
...Oh, my bad. I was spaced out. Did you need me？
Not that I need something, but... nevermind. Bye.
Is there something on my face？
You know... you have no shame, do you？
What is this sense of distance...
Why are you so far away？
Don't you look at me too much？ It's not that I don't like it...
I don't know what to do... when you stay silent like that...
What... do you want to get closer to Rinko？
You don't have to go that far away...
(Am I getting to used to this...)
(I think it might have been something awkward...)
That's about as much as I can spare.
Heh... well, I guess it's not that surprising.
Oh, it could be a great...
I see... you do that a lot？
It's not good to be worried about it.
That's fine. It's nothing to worry about.
I guess we don't have any other choice, right？
Don't be discouraged. It can't be helped.
Not that it matters to me...
Whatever... what are you going to do？
Come on, what are you going to do？
Hey, what are you going to do？
Well, let's see how it goes.
Hehe, show me the best part.
How is the tennis club, is it fun？
Yes, it is. Our club is not that strict, and it's fun.
Are you interested？ A little surprising, ▲小早川＊▲...
I don't like to move my body. Just curious.
...That boys and girls seem to get along too.
That kind of, what do you call it, interaction, isn't there something like that for you too？
I don't know... I don't think it's that bad...
Is a part-time job hard？ Or is it fun？
Are you interested？ I remember you were looking for a part-time job, ▲小早川＊▲...
That's not what I meant. Don't get the wrong idea on your own.
I'm talking about whether or not you are having fun.
Well, I guess it's fun... sometimes it can be a pain in the ass.
Hmm... are there a lot of girls in family dinners？
Yeah. I don't know about other places, but ours might be pretty common.
Nothing. You really look like you're having fun！
Is your class a friendly one？
I don't know... I think it's a good one.
You moved in halfway through the school year. I wonder if you fit in.
Haha, I'm not in trouble enough to worry you ▲小早川＊▲.
What's with that tone, it's hurtful.
Rinko is pretty well integrated into the class now, too.
If you're worried, do you want to come see me？ Onii-chan！
What is it like to live alone？
Oh. Well, I'm taking it easy.
Yeah？ You want to come check it out？
Nothing. You're the one who's thinking something weird, aren't you？
You're inviting a cute kouhai to your room... like that.
Eh？ Wrong, that's not what I intended！
Hehe, you panicked. I'm just kidding.
Visiting a senpai's home sounds like fun, though.
There's a senior girl in the tennis club who is a good friend of yours, right？
I heard that there is a senpai who is good friends with you at your part-time job.
Hmm. So you're friendly with them？
What, I knew that was the case...
But you know, Rinko is also... rather friendly... with you.
Well, we do talk sometimes. If anything, you are probably closer to me, ▲小早川＊▲.
Eh？ ...Hmm, I see... I guess so.
Let me ask you one thing.
You know, there's a girl on the tennis club that you're really close with.
You know, I heard that you have a good friend who is a senpai at your part-time job.
I knew it... Are you really that close？
Does that person talk more often than Rinko？
Yeah. I might talk more often with you, ▲小早川＊▲.
There's something that's been bothering me.
I heard there's a girl in the tennis club that you are good friends with.
I heard there's a senpai who is good friends with you at your part-time job.
The fact that his name comes up right away... it means she's a good friend of yours.
What's wrong？ You and Rinko are good friends, aren't we？
Not that we don't get along, but I'm a lot closer to you. And that0s true, ▲小早川＊▲.
How are you... when you're with Rinko？
Rinko, you know, she feels pretty comfortable around you...
Yes, I was wondering about you.
I was just trying to say your name.
Hey, hey... I'm going to ask you something weird.
Do you think Rinko has become a bit more feminine lately？
Um, if you don't think so, that's fine.
I'm a little conscious of it myself... hehe.
(Used bookstore, huh... might find something interesting...)
I knew it was you. Yo, ▲小早川＊▲.
Why, I'm just hanging out and... yeah, I'm on the Library Committee, too！ I came here to love books.
Rinko is doing the same. I'm looking for a book. There are some good books here.
If you're interested, I can explain.
And even in these times, it's still a bit different from the Beat Generation writers...
Well, it's been quite a while, can't we do this another time？ The guy at the store is smiling at you.
Eh, I haven't told you the best part yet.
I'll ask you about that again when we do our committee work. Come on, we're both there.
Oh, thank you for your kind words today.
No problem... thanks to you too.
It's been a long time since I've talked this much to someone. You are kind of like that... You are easy to talk to.
(I like that you enjoy it, ▲小早川＊▲...)
(Music store, huh... there are a lot of CD's...)
Yo, that's a coincidence. What do you want to do at a music store？
It's not that I'm here for...
You always listen to music. Do you make your own, ▲小早川＊▲？
...Well, I used to play guitar a little bit.
Um... I can play it, or rather... well, yeah？
That's great, let me hear you play a little bit.
Okay, I'm done tuning, so here you go.
No, I'm checking the weight of the guitar, the grip of the neck.
How was it？ You know, the guitar.
Heh, that's all you can say.
(She seems to be in a hurry... I wonder if I did something wrong...)
(Well, I think I'm going to go home soon...)
Haha, what's that. That's not the case, is it, ▲小早川＊▲？
It's fine. It's nice to relax once in a while.
Maybe. It seems pleasant, so I'll hang out with you.
Hang out you say, but I'm not doing anything.
You said you were spacing out.
I wonder why. I feel at home next to you.
Is that so？ Me too, ▲小早川＊▲.
You really are like an onii-chan, aren't you？
Age may be one thing, but... isn't the only thing.
I'm sure you're like that because it's you.
It's okay, even if you don't understand.
Hehe. Then, it'll be a secret.
Rinko has to go now. Bye-bye.
(Well, today, I'll be working hard as a Library Committee member...)
That attitude, it's really not possible.
Right？ Ah, geez, I'm so pissed off！
Hey, did you get in trouble with someone？
Sorry if I'm wrong... but I was wondering if that might be the case.
I'm in a bad mood. Don't talk to me.
Bad mood, huh... I knew it, is something wrong？
...those stupid girls were playing with their cell phones in the library. Beep, beep, beep without even turning off the sound.
I told them not to use the school's facilities if they are too stupid to have good manners. And by the way, your make-up is so bad, it doesn't suit you at all.
What's that？ You're on that idiot's side, too.
No. It's not that, but if you talk like that, you'll make a lot of enemies.
(I know it's a little late, but I think I'll do something...)
Again, walking out alone at this hour...
What's with you. Are you in the student council？
I'm on the Library Cmte！ Besides... here, you might meet that guy you were tangled up with before.
Not really... I'm attentive to the people around me.
I don't think so. You don't have to go out of your way to cross a dangerous bridge.
You have no choice, huh... You still don't want to stay home.
I'll hang out with you for a while, so let's get out of here. Agreed？
Eh？ Why... well, if you're going home, that's fine.
The president of the council is too noisy. I'm not in the mood to play.
Library Committee member！ No problem. I'll take you home then.
Hah... you can follow me if you want.
It's like you're following me around.
(It seems dangerous, better wait and see...)
(And again, someone who looks like trouble...)
I knew it, I can't leave her alone！
(It was fine before, and it will be fine if I leave them alone...)
(Oh, looks like you managed it again...)
Who are you bastard？ Are you her boyfriend？
Yes. We're on a date right now.
That's right！ And he's so strong！
I'm talking about you！ Go there and beat him！
Heh... nii-san, so you want to beat me？
I'm going to work as a member of the Library Committee today, too！
What's wrong with you, now... and you're in plain clothes, ▲小早川＊▲！
(She didn't go home... she was still in her uniform at the convenience store.)
(I knew it had something to do with the crying on the rooftop...)
(Still, if you're coming all the way to the library, maybe you're relying on me...)
Ah, I see. I'll go then.
You're in plain clothes again, what happened, ▲小早川＊▲！？
Okay, I'll ask her out on a date
Hey, are you free this Sunday？
Well, you know... what do you think about going on a date？
Da... date means... with whom and who.
...what are you talking about, you idiot...
I-I see... well, I guess that was expected.
I don't mind going out with you.
It's not like a date or anything！ Look... we're just going out.
That's fine. So let's just go out, okay？
It's about time... I think I'm going to bed for the rest of the day！
"There is a canned mackerel called Premium Gold. -Rinko."
